<br><br>Christmas Jumper Day is a yearly fundraising initiative that encourages people to don their favourite festive jumpers and make a small donation to Save the Children. Since its inception in 2012, this campaign has raised over £30 million to provide essential resources like food, healthcare, and education for children worldwide.<br>
<br>In 2024, Shaun the Sheep, the beloved animated character, has been appointed as the campaign's "Head of Wool," adding an extra touch of charm and creativity to the event.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-31_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-32_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-33_">The theme for 2024 - Sustainability and community engagement</h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS ckDBXz pf-35_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-c49d09f2-fede-4d40-ab04-abfe13d7568b"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">This year’s theme highlights sustainability and community involvement. Participants are encouraged to wear upcycled, pre-loved, or second-hand Christmas jumpers, reducing waste and promoting environmentally friendly practices. By reusing or customising old sweaters, participants can celebrate the festive season responsibly while making a positive impact.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-38_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-39_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-40_">Key facts and statistics
